We define the number of opsin molecules in each state multiplied by their relative, normalized transmembrane currents as the ‘Effective ChR2 concentration per axon’. We define the likelihood of eliciting an action potential (AP) as being directly proportional to the cumulative transmembrane current of all opsins.3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
